# Understanding CRUD

Most backend applications perform four common operations.

These are known as **CRUD**.

| Letter | Meaning | Example           |
| ------ | ------- | ----------------- |
| C      | Create  | Add a new product |
| R      | Read    | View products     |
| U      | Update  | Edit a product    |
| D      | Delete  | Remove a product  |

For products, these operations eventually become:

| Method | Endpoint        | Purpose          |
| ------ | --------------- | ---------------- |
| GET    | `/products`     | Get all products |
| GET    | `/products/:id` | Get one product  |
| POST   | `/products`     | Create a product |
| PUT    | `/products/:id` | Update a product |
| DELETE | `/products/:id` | Delete a product |

At this stage, the endpoints only return messages because the application is not yet connected to a database.

